The Stock Exchange of Singapore hasdecided to discontinue a 150 mln dlr standby credit facilityfor broking firms facing financial problems because of thefailure of Pan-Electric Industries Ltd, an exchange statementsaid.    The credit line from four local banks was set up onDecember 3, 1985 to bail out firms involved in forwardcontracts with Pan-Electric, which went into receivership inNovember 1985 owing 390 mln dlrs. The company was wound up lastyear.    Local broking houses have been contributing a 0.125 pctlevy on share transactions to the scheme but will no longer doso, the statement said. REUTER&#3;